@startuml
title Use Case 4: Sending a Message

actor Sender as "User (Sender)"
boundary GUI as "Client GUI"
boundary cGUI as "Recipient GUI"
control Client as "Client App"
countrol Recipient as "Recipient Client"
control Server as "Server"
collections Cache as "Server Cache"

== Compose and send ==
Sender -> GUI: Type message\nClick "Send"
GUI -> Client: PassMessage(MessageObject)
Client -> Client: Update local conversation
Client --> GUI: Repaint conversation
Client -> Server: SendMessage(MessageObject)

== Server processing ==
Server -> Cache: Append message to conversation and lookup participants 
Cache --> Server: Participant list + online status
Server -> Server: Check Online participants' active conversation 
Server --> Cache: Add conversation to participant's unread conversations\nfor all participants whose active conversation is not this conversation
== Delivery to online recipients ==
loop For each logged-in recipient
  Server --> Client: PushMessage(conversationId,\n messageId, messagePayload)
  Client -> GUI: Display new message
end
@enduml
